</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="C1CD4D2EFFE4FF96FEE9F898FD0D0536" authority="Laporte, 1840" authorityName="Laporte" authorityYear="1840" box="[301,644,1886,1908]" class="Insecta" family="Lycidae" genus="Lycus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="17" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="mirabilis">
<emphasis id="34B9EABFFFE4FF96FEE9F898FE540536" box="[301,477,1886,1908]" italics="true" pageId="17">Lycus mirabilis</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="625C4B5CFFE4FF96FE20F898FD0D0536" author="Laporte FLNC" box="[484,644,1886,1908]" pageId="17" pagination="1 - 324" refId="ref16424" refString="Laporte FLNC. 1840. Histoire naturelle des insectes Coleopteres; avec une introduction renfermant l'anatomie et la physiologie des animaux articules, par M. Brulle. Tome premier. Histoire naturelle des animaux articules, annelides, crustaces, arachnides, myriapodes et insectes. Paris: P. Dumenil, 1 - 324." type="book chapter" year="1840">Laporte, 1840</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
. 
<emphasis id="34B9EABFFFE4FF96FCEDF9C6FC1F045C" box="[809,918,1537,1561]" italics="true" pageId="17">Remarks</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="067236ADFFE4FF95FCEDF9EEFE4A041C" blockId="17.[809,1425,1577,1906]" lastBlockId="18.[163,779,1359,1626]" lastPageId="18" pageId="17">
The genus name 
<taxonomicName id="C1CD4D2EFFE4FF96FC2BF9EEFBC3047B" authorityName="Laporte" authorityYear="1840" box="[1007,1098,1577,1598]" class="Insecta" family="Lycidae" genus="Celiasis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="17" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="34B9EABFFFE4FF96FC2BF9EEFBC3047B" box="[1007,1098,1577,1598]" italics="true" pageId="17">Celiasis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has not been used except in old literature and catalogues (
<bibRefCitation id="625C4B5CFFE4FF96FB44F98FFABD0418" author="Bourgeois JM" box="[1152,1332,1608,1630]" pageId="17" pagination="lix - lxii" refId="ref15208" refString="Bourgeois JM. 1883. [Communication]. Bulletin de la Societe entomologique de France 1883: lix - lxii." type="journal article" year="1883">Bourgeois, 1883</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="625C4B5CFFE4FF96FA85F98FFCEB0439" author="Kleine R" pageId="17" pagination="1 - 145" refId="ref16220" refString="Kleine R. 1933. Lycidae. In Junk W, Schenkling S, eds. Coleopterorum Catalogus, Pars 128. Berlin: W. Junk, 1 - 145." type="book chapter" year="1933">Kleine, 1933</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="625C4B5CFFE4FF96FCB5F9A1FBC20439" author="Blackwelder RE" box="[881,1099,1638,1660]" pageId="17" pagination="343 - 551" refId="ref14773" refString="Blackwelder RE. 1945. Checklist of the coleopterous insects of Mexico, Central America, The West Indies, and South America. Part 3. Bulletin of the United States National Museum 185: 343 - 551." type="journal article" year="1945">Blackwelder, 1945</bibRefCitation>
). This genus was proposed in a short note attached to the description of 
<taxonomicName id="C1CD4D2EFFE4FF96FA8AF941FBB804FC" authority="Laporte, 1840" authorityName="Laporte" authorityYear="1840" class="Insecta" family="Lycidae" genus="Lycus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="17" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="mirabilis">
<emphasis id="34B9EABFFFE4FF96FA8AF941FC1804FC" italics="true" pageId="17">Lycus mirabilis</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="625C4B5CFFE4FF96FC52F963FBB804FC" author="Laporte FLNC" box="[918,1073,1700,1721]" pageId="17" pagination="1 - 324" refId="ref16424" refString="Laporte FLNC. 1840. Histoire naturelle des insectes Coleopteres; avec une introduction renfermant l'anatomie et la physiologie des animaux articules, par M. Brulle. Tome premier. Histoire naturelle des animaux articules, annelides, crustaces, arachnides, myriapodes et insectes. Paris: P. Dumenil, 1 - 324." type="book chapter" year="1840">Laporte, 1840</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
from Columbia. 
<bibRefCitation id="625C4B5CFFE4FF96FB2FF963FA1804FF" author="Laporte FLNC" box="[1259,1425,1700,1722]" pageId="17" pagination="1 - 324" refId="ref16424" refString="Laporte FLNC. 1840. Histoire naturelle des insectes Coleopteres; avec une introduction renfermant l'anatomie et la physiologie des animaux articules, par M. Brulle. Tome premier. Histoire naturelle des animaux articules, annelides, crustaces, arachnides, myriapodes et insectes. Paris: P. Dumenil, 1 - 324." type="book chapter" year="1840">Laporte (1840)</bibRefCitation>
characterized it as an insect with a triangular head terminating in a point, an almost rectangular pronotum and dilated, convex elytra. The original specimen was in Laporteâ€™s collection destroyed in 1843 (
<bibRefCitation id="625C4B5CFFE4FF96FAD8F8D9FCE80517" author="Evenhuis NL" pageId="17" pagination="53 - 63" refId="ref15622" refString="Evenhuis NL. 2012. Francois-Louis Comte de Castelnau (1802 - 1880) and the mysterious disappearance of his original insect collection. Zootaxa 3168: 53 - 63." type="journal article" year="2012">Evenhuis, 2012</bibRefCitation>
), and we do not have access to any Columbian species resembling 
<taxonomicName id="C1CD4D2EFFE4FF96FBD5F89BFA180534" authority="Laporte, 1840" authorityName="Laporte" authorityYear="1840" box="[1041,1425,1884,1905]" class="Insecta" family="Lycidae" genus="Celiasis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="17" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="mirabilis">
<emphasis id="34B9EABFFFE4FF96FBD5F89BFB6D0534" box="[1041,1252,1884,1905]" italics="true" pageId="17">Celiasis mirabilis</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="625C4B5CFFE4FF96FB29F89BFA180534" author="Laporte FLNC" box="[1261,1425,1884,1905]" pageId="17" pagination="1 - 324" refId="ref16424" refString="Laporte FLNC. 1840. Histoire naturelle des insectes Coleopteres; avec une introduction renfermant l'anatomie et la physiologie des animaux articules, par M. Brulle. Tome premier. Histoire naturelle des animaux articules, annelides, crustaces, arachnides, myriapodes et insectes. Paris: P. Dumenil, 1 - 324." type="book chapter" year="1840">Laporte, 1840</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
because this genus has never been reported again. Its distribution and phenetic similarity raise the possibility that 
<taxonomicName id="C1CD4D2EFFE7FF95FF1EFA4BFEB607E4" authorityName="Bourgeois" authorityYear="1883" box="[218,319,1420,1441]" class="Insecta" family="Coleoptera (awaiting allocation)" genus="Neolycus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="18" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="34B9EABFFFE7FF95FF1EFA4BFEB607E4" box="[218,319,1420,1441]" italics="true" pageId="18">Neolycus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="C1CD4D2EFFE7FF95FEBEFA4BFE5D07E4" authorityName="Laporte" authorityYear="1840" box="[378,468,1420,1441]" class="Insecta" family="Lycidae" genus="Celiasis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="18" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="34B9EABFFFE7FF95FEBEFA4BFE5D07E4" box="[378,468,1420,1441]" italics="true" pageId="18">Celiasis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are congeneric. Given that we cannot designate the 
<typeStatus id="D976880FFFE7FF95FE1FFA6CFDB50785" box="[475,572,1451,1472]" pageId="18">neotype</typeStatus>
, which would be necessary for the stability of the nomenclature, we have to keep this taxon as a 
<emphasis id="34B9EABFFFE7FF95FDC1FA2EFD3307B8" box="[517,698,1512,1534]" italics="true" pageId="18">nomen dubium</emphasis>
in the classification. Only new specimens from Columbia can provide further information about its relationships to other Neotropical genera.
</paragraph>
